.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH codeaegis 1  "codeaegis " 
.SH NAME
codeaegis \- CodeAegis Local Security Scanner & Workspace Agent Skill
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcodeaegis\fR [\fB\-\-logs\fR] [\fB\-m\fR|\fB\-\-model\fR] [\fB\-\-auth\fR] [\fB\-\-scanners\fR] [\fB\-\-skip\-scanners\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
CodeAegis Local Security Scanner & Workspace Agent Skill
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-logs\fR
Enable quality logging for scan results and critic decisions
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-model\fR \fI<MODEL>\fR
Override the LLM model to use
.TP
\fB\-\-auth\fR
Setup LLM authorization or view current LLM config info
.TP
\fB\-\-scanners\fR \fI<SCANNERS>\fR
Comma\-separated list of security scanners to enable (trufflehog, osv, trivy, opengrep). If omitted, all are enabled
.TP
\fB\-\-skip\-scanners\fR \fI<SKIP_SCANNERS>\fR
Comma\-separated list of security scanners to disable
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
codeaegis\-watch(1)
Monitors a directory for file changes and scans them automatically
.TP
codeaegis\-init(1)
Setup a Workspace Agent Skill for CodeAegis in a directory
.TP
codeaegis\-lsp(1)
Runs the CodeAegis Language Server (LSP)
.TP
codeaegis\-scan(1)
Scans directories or files for vulnerabilities
.TP
codeaegis\-auth(1)
Manage LLM authentication credentials in the OS keychain
.TP
codeaegis\-exclude(1)
Exclude a file or directory pattern from scans
.TP
codeaegis\-setup(1)
Interactive configuration wizard to set up credentials, exclusions, and skills
.TP
codeaegis\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
